registry.title: IETF XML Registry
registry.note:
defines an IANA maintained registry of XML documents used within IETF protocols. These documents are divided into classes: XML Namespaces, Document Type Declarations, Schemas, and RDF Schemas. Individual documents are then registered within each class. The class and document names are combined to form a name which is then used within the 'urn:ietf:params:xml' portion of the IANA maintained URN space for protocol parameters.
This registry is intended for:
(1) identifiers whose use is described in an IETF specification, and
(2) identifiers that are allocated in IETF-controlled URI space, such as "urn:ietf:..." and/or "http://...ietf.org/..."
The registration template should cite the specification.
The list of classes is provided below.
